{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01H65X6QkvgSYpJRMtSKXH4p","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# KAIROS Contract Spec (Rust)\n2\t\n3\t## 1. Objective\n4\t\n5\tDefine Rust rewrite contract for KAIROS family (`KAIROS`, `KAIROS_BRIEF`, `KAIROS_CHANNELS`) with stable prompt/routing/telemetry boundaries.\n6\t\n7\t## 2. Current Code Evidence\n8\t\n9\t1. `main.tsx:80`, `81` (assistant module + gate import)\n10\t2. `main.tsx:2206` (assistant mode prompt path)\n11\t3. `main.tsx:1728` (tool visibility with KAIROS/BRIEF)\n12\t4. `utils/processUserInput/processSlashCommand.tsx:102` (slash routing behavior)\n13\t5. `commands.ts:63`, `67`, `70` (feature-gated command registration)\n14\t6. `services/analytics/metadata.ts:735` (`kairosActive` emission)\n15\t\n16\t## 3. Rust Boundary Mapping\n17\t\n18\t1. `api-types`: mode flags, routing decisions, analytics tag schema.\n19\t2. `app-services`: activation policy and routing orchestration.\n20\t3. `tool-runtime`: mode-aware tool visibility policy.\n21\t4. `ui-tui`: prompt composition and slash entry behavior.\n22\t5. `config`: feature gate keys and default mode settings.\n23\t\n24\t## 4. Proposed Contracts\n25\t\n26\t```rust\n27\tpub trait AssistantModeService: Send + Sync {\n28\t    fn resolve_mode(&self, ctx: AssistantModeContext) -> AssistantModeDecision;\n29\t    fn build_prompt(&self, ctx: PromptComposeContext) -> PromptComposeResult;\n30\t    fn route_input(&self, ctx: RouteInputContext) -> RouteDecision;\n31\t}\n32\t```\n33\t\n34\tPolicy requirements:\n35\t\n36\t1. Prompt precedence order is deterministic and documented.\n37\t2. Tool visibility is a pure function of mode + capability policy.\n38\t3. Telemetry tag emission uses schema-only fields (no payload leakage).\n39\t\n40\t## 5. Error Taxonomy\n41\t\n42\t```rust\n43\tpub enum KairosError {\n44\t    DisabledByPolicy,\n45\t    InvalidModeState,\n46\t    PromptComposeFailed(String),\n47\t    RouteConflict,\n48\t}\n49\t```\n50\t\n51\t## 6. Constants Classification\n52\t\n53\t1. `api-types`: mode labels and telemetry field keys.\n54\t2. `config`: feature gate keys and mode defaults.\n55\t3. `core-domain`: route and precedence invariants.\n56\t4. `ui-tui`: display copy and helper text.\n57\t\n58\t## 7. Acceptance Matrix\n59\t\n60\t1. Contract tests: mode resolution and route precedence are deterministic.\n61\t2. Integration tests: KAIROS/BRIEF/CHANNELS combinations produce expected tool visibility.\n62\t3. CLI behavior tests: slash routing and assistant-mode entry behavior match current semantics.\n63\t\n64\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_013X19bThc964g3DNsp4No5N","session_id":"6362e84a-6f04-4b0f-bbe9-0adfe63953c5","uuid":"d6e40ad9-ab9f-4477-b622-b949aeae6f0e","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:31:53.370Z"}
