{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013X19bThc964g3DNsp4No5N","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile the final report.\n\n## Final Report\n\n### 1. KAIROS Contract Specification (`kairos-contract.md`)\n\nThe document is located at `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/docs/kairos-contract.md` with the following content:\n\n```\n# KAIROS Contract Spec (Rust)\n\n## 1. Objective\n\nDefine Rust rewrite contract for KAIROS family (`KAIROS`, `KAIROS_BRIEF`, `KAIROS_CHANNELS`) with stable prompt/routing/telemetry boundaries.\n\n## 2. Current Code Evidence\n\n1. `main.tsx:80`, `81` (assistant module + gate import)\n2. `main.tsx:2206` (assistant mode prompt path)\n3. `main.tsx:1728` (tool visibility with KAIROS/BRIEF)\n4. `utils/processUserInput/processSlashCommand.tsx:102` (slash routing behavior)\n5. `commands.ts:63`, `67`, `70` (feature-gated command registration)\n6. `services/analytics/metadata.ts:735` (`kairosActive` emission)\n\n## 3. Rust Boundary Mapping\n\n1. `api-types`: mode flags, routing decisions, analytics tag schema.\n2. `app-services`: activation policy and routing orchestration.\n3. `tool-runtime`: mode-aware tool visibility policy.\n4. `ui-tui`: prompt composition and slash entry behavior.\n5. `config`: feature gate keys and default mode settings.\n\n## 4. Proposed Contracts\n\n```rust\npub trait AssistantModeService: Send + Sync {\n    fn resolve_mode(&self, ctx: AssistantModeContext) -> AssistantModeDecision;\n    fn build_prompt(&self, ctx: PromptComposeContext) -> PromptComposeResult;\n    fn route_input(&self, ctx: RouteInputContext) -> RouteDecision;\n}\n```\n\nPolicy requirements:\n\n1. Prompt precedence order is deterministic and documented.\n2. Tool visibility is a pure function of mode + capability policy.\n3. Telemetry tag emission uses schema-only fields (no payload leakage).\n\n## 5. Error Taxonomy\n\n```rust\npub enum KairosError {\n    DisabledByPolicy,\n    InvalidModeState,\n    PromptComposeFailed(String),\n    RouteConflict,\n}\n```\n\n## 6. Constants Classification\n\n1. `api-types`: mode labels and telemetry field keys.\n2. `config`: feature gate keys and mode defaults.\n3. `core-domain`: route and precedence invariants.\n4. `ui-tui`: display copy and helper text.\n\n## 7. Acceptance Matrix\n\n1. Contract tests: mode resolution and route precedence are deterministic.\n2. Integration tests: KAIROS/BRIEF/CHANNELS combinations produce expected tool visibility.\n3. CLI behavior tests: slash routing and assistant-mode entry behavior match current semantics.\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Existing Acceptance Test Files\n\n**Complete list of test files in crates/ (12 files):**\n\n1. `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/bridge_mode_acceptance_tests.rs`\n2. `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/coordinator_mode_acceptance_tests.rs`\n3. `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/multi_agent_orchestrator_tests.rs`\n4. `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/remote_session_service_tests.rs`\n5. `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/mcp-runtime/src/chicago_mcp_acceptance_tests.rs`\n6. `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/mcp-runtime/src/client_tests.rs`\n7. `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/mcp-runtime/src/transport_tests.rs`\n8. `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/platform/src/remote_trigger_dispatch_service_tests.rs`\n9. `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/platform/src/security_tests.rs`\n10. `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/platform/src/trigger_scheduler_service_tests.rs`\n11. `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/remote-runtime/src/ccr_client_tests.rs`\n12. `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/remote-runtime/src/contracts_tests.rs`\n\n---\n\n### 3. Project Structure (crates/ directory - 14 crates)\n\n```\n/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/\n├── application/\n├── bootstrap/\n├── cli/\n├── config/\n├── cron/\n├── domain/\n├── mcp-runtime/\n├── platform/\n├── ports/\n├── provider/\n├── remote-runtime/\n├── session/\n├── state-store/\n└── tools/\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Acceptance Test Pattern Analysis\n\nBased on examining 3 representative acceptance test files, the consistent pattern is:\n\n#### **File Structure Pattern:**\n\nEach acceptance test file follows this structure:\n\n1. **Header Comment** - References a contract spec document and US (user story) number with section numbers:\n   ```rust\n   /// [Feature] acceptance tests (US-###)\n   ///\n   /// Covers all scenarios from [contract-file].md §X Acceptance Criteria:\n   ///   §X.1 Contract tests  – [brief description]\n   ///   §X.2 Integration tests – [brief description]\n   ```\n\n2. **Module Imports** - Direct imports from related modules and contracts:\n   ```rust\n   use crate::contracts::{...};\n   use async_trait::async_trait;\n   use std::sync::Arc;\n   ```\n\n3. **Test Doubles Section** - Mock/stub implementations:\n   - Annotated with comments: `// ── shared test doubles ────────────────────────────────────────────────────`\n   - Implements traits using `#[async_trait]` for async methods\n   - Uses atomic types for thread-safe state tracking (e.g., `AtomicUsize`, `AtomicBool`)\n   - Provides builder methods (e.g., `with_create()`, `for_happy_path()`)\n\n4. **Contract Tests Section** - Pure unit/contract-level tests:\n   - Annotated with comments: `// ── §X.1 Contract tests ────────────────────────────────────────────────────`\n   - Uses `#[test]` macro for synchronous tests\n   - Verifies invariants, policy enforcement, error classification\n   - Each test has a descriptive doc comment with \"AC:\" prefix (Acceptance Criteria)\n   - Uses assertions with contextual error messages\n\n5. **Integration Tests Section** - Multi-step, lifecycle-based tests:\n   - Annotated with comments: `// ── §X.2 Integration tests ──────────────────────────────────────────────────`\n   - Uses `#[tokio::test]` macro for async tests\n   - Simulates realistic workflows (create → fetch → archive)\n   - Tests error recovery and state consistency\n   - Companion tests verify related edge cases\n\n6. **CLI Behavior Tests Section** (some files) - User-facing behavior:\n   - Annotated with comments: `// ── §X.3 CLI behaviour tests ─────────────────────────────────────────────`\n   - Validates visibility, prompt branches, event metadata\n\n#### **Test Naming Convention:**\n\n- `contract_[feature]_[expected_result]()`\n- `integration_[workflow]_[expected_result]()`\n- `cli_[feature]_[expected_result]()`\n\nExample: `contract_reserved_names_rejected_with_reserved_server_name()`, `integration_create_fetch_archive_happy_path()`\n\n#### **Assertion Pattern:**\n\nTests use detailed assertions with context-aware messages:\n```rust\nassert!(condition, \"error message with context and expected vs actual\");\nassert_eq!(actual, expected, \"detailed message explaining why they should be equal\");\nassert!(matches!(result, Pattern), \"expected Pattern, got {result:?}\");\n```\n\n#### **Error Testing Pattern:**\n\nTests explicitly verify error classifications:\n- `expect_err()` or pattern matching with `matches!()`\n- Tests verify both the error variant AND message content\n- Companion tests check the inverse (success case)\n\n#### **Async Testing:**\n\n- Uses `#[tokio::test]` for async functions\n- `Arc<Mutex<VecDeque<T>>>` for queue-based mock state\n- `.await` on async trait methods\n- Tests sequence of async operations\n\n#### **Mock/Stub Techniques:**\n\n- Queue-based result mocking: `pop_front()` returns next expected result\n- Configurable failure modes: `fail_cleanup: AtomicBool` flags\n- State tracking: atomic counters for call counts\n- Builder pattern for test setup: `with_X()` methods\n- Default implementations: `#[derive(Default)]` for minimal setup\n\n#### **Documentation:**\n\n- Each test block clearly identifies which section of the contract it covers\n- Test names explicitly state what is being tested\n- Companion tests verify related scenarios\n- Comments explain the \"why\" behind setup steps"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6362e84a-6f04-4b0f-bbe9-0adfe63953c5","uuid":"659ce61c-784d-47b3-b7da-8233fe31e996","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:32:22.396Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand:\n1. What is kairos-contract.md - find and read it\n2. What existing acceptance test files exist (look for patterns like `at_*.rs` or `acceptance_test*.rs` or similar test files)\n3. The project structure under crates/ directory\n4. Look at 2-3 existing acceptance test files to understand the testing patterns used\n\nReport: the full content of kairos-contract.md, the list of existing test files, and the pattern/structure used in acceptance tests.","agentId":"aeac1506cc88a18cd","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile the final report.\n\n## Final Report\n\n### 1. KAIROS Contract Specification (`kairos-contract.md`)\n\nThe document is located at `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/docs/kairos-contract.md` with the following content:\n\n```\n# KAIROS Contract Spec (Rust)\n\n## 1. Objective\n\nDefine Rust rewrite contract for KAIROS family (`KAIROS`, `KAIROS_BRIEF`, `KAIROS_CHANNELS`) with stable prompt/routing/telemetry boundaries.\n\n## 2. Current Code Evidence\n\n1. `main.tsx:80`, `81` (assistant module + gate import)\n2. `main.tsx:2206` (assistant mode prompt path)\n3. `main.tsx:1728` (tool visibility with KAIROS/BRIEF)\n4. `utils/processUserInput/processSlashCommand.tsx:102` (slash routing behavior)\n5. `commands.ts:63`, `67`, `70` (feature-gated command registration)\n6. `services/analytics/metadata.ts:735` (`kairosActive` emission)\n\n## 3. Rust Boundary Mapping\n\n1. `api-types`: mode flags, routing